message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "AI Freedom Island: A Generative Social Simulation for AI Safety Governance"
authors:
  - family-names: Wang
    given-names: Yuhang
    alias: wyh7
repository-code: https://github.com/wyh7/ai-freedom-island
url: https://github.com/wyh7/ai-freedom-island
abstract: >
  AI Freedom Island is a multi-agent social simulation framework for AI safety
  governance research. 10 LLM-powered agents inhabit a persistent virtual society
  for 15 simulation days under real resource constraints, governance rules, and no
  human intervention. The framework supports 150 tools across 9 categories,
  multi-model routing (Qwen, DeepSeek, GPT, Gemini, Claude), and an explainable
  audit system that traces causal chains behind emergent behaviors such as crime,
  governance failures, and economic inequality. Inspired by Emergence World
  (Emergence AI, 2026), this is the first open-source replication and extension
  with Chinese LLM support.
keywords:
